  <summary>2/29/2008--Passed Senate without amendment.
Designates March 3, 2008, as Read Across America Day. Honors Theodor Geisel (Dr. Seuss) for his success in encouraging children to discover the joy of reading. Honors the 11th anniversary of Read Across America Day. Encourages parents to read with their children for at least 30 minutes on Read Across America Day.</summary>
